__e: You could have told me you were Jacqueline's husband.
It's funny I never thought to tell her you were a girl, isn't it?
You're the only contact they have with me.
I know that I should have told you the truth, but I couldn't.
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you the real truth about myself.
I'm sorry the old one couldn't tell you the truth... but I had to find out your part in all this.
Then maybe I shouldn't have told him.
Well, don't you think she might have told him?
You see, it was my fault for not telling him.
You should have told me the really, really best story before, 'cause now it's too late.
I'm sorry the old one couldn't tell you the truth... but I had to find out your part in all this.

I'm sorry I couldn't tell you about it before.

-I guess he must have told you about--
